answers.body_markdown:
You could set the `html` and `body` to a height of 100% and `background-attachment: fixed` on the body to keep the background image from scrolling:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    html,
    body {
      height: 100%;
    }

    body {
      background-image: url(//placekitten.com/1920/1080);
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-size: cover;
      background-attachment: fixed;
    }

    div.alpha.layer {
      background-color: #ffffff70;
      margin: 20px 10px;
      height: 1500px;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;alpha layer&quot; ; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

